tribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[Ἀ]ρισταρχου̣ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[.]ΡΙΣΤΑΡΧΟ.\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004419_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004419_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004419.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004419-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text based upon photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [Ἀ]ρ̣ι̣σ̣ταρχο̣υ̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Aristarchos\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis display a single name in the genitive. However, given the fragmentary state of this stone, it cannot be ruled out that this is the patronymic of the deceased, with a first name on the now lost upper portion of the stone. Against this, the second plinth from this funerary monument (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004420\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004420\u003C/a>) clearly contains only a single name in the genitive, and it is therefore more likely that only the single name was also recorded here. The evidence of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004416\u003C/a> and of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004417\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004418\u003C/a> suggests that the two individuals commemorated by this stone and its pair ISic004420 were related (bothers?). The name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%E1%BC%88%CF%81%CE%AF%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B1%CF%81%CF%87%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀρίσταρχος\u003C/a> is widely attested, including c.11 attestations in Sicily (all from the eastern half of the island).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 108 no.9 and fig.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Somewhat irregular plainly cut, widely spaced letters. Rho has closed and regular eye; sigma has horizontal upper and lower strokes, the intermediate strokes joined by a curve; alpha is broad with straight bar; omicron is small and mid-line.\u003C/p> Line 1  30  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[187,190,193,196,199,202,205,208],{"id":188,"html":189},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[Ἀ]ρισταρχου̣ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[.]ΡΙΣΤΑΡΧΟ.\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":191,"html":192},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004419_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004419_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004419.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004419-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":194,"html":195},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text based upon photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [Ἀ]ρ̣ι̣σ̣ταρχο̣υ̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":197,"html":198},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Aristarchos\u003C/p>  ",{"id":200,"html":201},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis display a single name in the genitive. However, given the fragmentary state of this stone, it cannot be ruled out that this is the patronymic of the deceased, with a first name on the now lost upper portion of the stone. Against this, the second plinth from this funerary monument (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004420\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004420\u003C/a>) clearly contains only a single name in the genitive, and it is therefore more likely that only the single name was also recorded here. The evidence of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004416\u003C/a> and of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004417\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004418\u003C/a> suggests that the two individuals commemorated by this stone and its pair ISic004420 were related (bothers?). The name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%E1%BC%88%CF%81%CE%AF%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B1%CF%81%CF%87%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀρίσταρχος\u003C/a> is widely attested, including c.11 attestations in Sicily (all from the eastern half of the island).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":203,"html":204},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 108 no.9 and fig.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":206,"html":207},"handnote","\u003Cp>Somewhat irregular plainly cut, widely spaced letters. Rho has closed and regular eye; sigma has horizontal upper and lower strokes, the intermediate strokes joined by a curve; alpha is broad with straight bar; omicron is small and mid-line.\u003C/p> Line 1  30  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  ",{"id":209,"html":210},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[212,214,217,218],{"html":213},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":215,"lang":128,"html":216},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[Ἀ]ρισταρχου̣ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":213},{"id":219,"lang":128,"html":220},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[.]ΡΙΣΤΑΡΧΟ.\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[222,224],{"image":104,"thumb":223,"title":107},"ISic004419_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":225,"thumb":226,"title":107},"ISic004419.jpg","ISic004419-thumb.jpg",[228],{"html":54},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph for Aristarchos\u003C/title>\n      