     \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Tripi\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"site\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/186\">Necropoli di Abakainon\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\"/>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Plinth (support for a stele) with moulding around the base. The plinth is heavily damaged and all the upper portion is lost and much of the lower moulding on the sides also; the lower part of the inscribed face is preserved, marked by a number of deep striations in the surface. The plinth is the left one of a pair mounted on a single base, classified as an epitymbion of type C.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone\" type=\"stone.unspecified\" subtype=\"unverified\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/75.html\">sandstone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.arch_element.plinth\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/1910.html\">plinth\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">18.5\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">51.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">52.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Remains of a single line of Greek letters, somewhat irregularly laid out and not following the horizontal\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Somewhat irregular plainly cut, widely spaced letters. Rho has closed and regular eye; sigma has horizontal upper and lower strokes, the intermediate strokes joined by a curve; alpha is broad with straight bar; omicron is small and mid-line.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"30\" atMost=\"30\">30\u003C/height>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">NA\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062\" corresp=\"#findspot\">Abacaenum\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003Coffset>near\n                                    \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2522853\">Tripi\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003C/offset>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.05191, 15.10158\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0350\" notAfter-custom=\"-0201\" evidence=\"archaeological-context\">The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE, offering a terminus ante quem\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" xml:id=\"findspot\">Tomb 105 of the necropolis in contrada Cardusa\u003Cgeo>38.065190, 15.114380\u003C/geo>, where it remains in situ\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Metcalfe 2016 visited site\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                 \u003Cchange when=\"2020-05-28\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created the file from template, publications, and photographs\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-09-10\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-21\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004419_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004419.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">Ἀ\u003C/supplied>ρισταρχο\u003Cunclear>υ\u003C/unclear>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n               \u003ClistApp>\n                   \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text based upon photographs\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                   \u003Capp loc=\"line 1\">\u003Cnote>Sofia 2018: [Ἀ]\u003Cunclear>ρισ\u003C/unclear>ταρχ\u003Cunclear>ου\u003C/unclear>\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n              \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>(tomb) of Aristarchos\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>The majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis display a single name in the genitive. However, given the fragmentary state of this stone, it cannot be ruled out that this is the patronymic of the deceased, with a first name on the now lost upper portion of the stone. Against this, the second plinth from this funerary monument (\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004420\">ISic004420\u003C/ref>) clearly contains only a single name in the genitive, and it is therefore more likely that only the single name was also recorded here. The evidence of \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\">ISic004415\u003C/ref>/\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\">ISic004416\u003C/ref> and of \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\">ISic004417\u003C/ref>/\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\">ISic004418\u003C/ref> suggests that the two individuals commemorated by this stone and its pair ISic004420 were related (bothers?). The name \u003Cref target=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%E1%BC%88%CF%81%CE%AF%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B1%CF%81%CF%87%CE%BF%CF%82\">Ἀρίσταρχος\u003C/ref> is widely attested, including c.11 attestations in Sicily (all from the eastern half of the island).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                   \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Sofia\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2018\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>108 no.9 and fig.10\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JQQKI6JP\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
